        explanation: "The module computes ~$350.63/day at 2048x2048 (2,805 tokens/image, 140.25M tokens/day) versus ~$31.88/day at 512x512 (255 tokens/image, 12.75M tokens/day), saving ~$318.75/day — an 11x token reduction, not 16x, because the flat 85-token overhead per image is proportionally larger at low resolution. Option A is correct. Option B is wrong because cost scales with tile count plus a flat overhead, not the linear resolution ratio. Option C is wrong because the flat 85-token overhead per image means token count does NOT track tile count exactly — the real reduction is 11x, not 16x. Option D is wrong because the module states providers bill per actual visual token consumed, so resolution materially changes cost.",
