    takeaway: "Red-teaming is systematic adversarial testing across every attack surface a deployed system exposes — not a pass of tricky prompts, and not the same scope as jailbreak-taxonomy's prompt-specific sub-taxonomy. Structured attack categories (prompt injection, jailbreak, data extraction, system prompt leak, hallucination elicitation, PII exposure) cover the failure modes that ad hoc testing misses. Run red-teaming before deployment, document every finding with attack vector and model response, and treat the taxonomy as a living artifact updated with new attack patterns.",
